# Llama 3 8B Instruct on TPU v7x — balanced 2K in / 2K out at 4K context.
#
# Why this case exists: the existing v7x cases (1800/128 prefill_heavy
# and 1024/1024 balanced) only use a quarter of the 8K context window
# and were sized for v6e operating points. v7x has 3x v6e HBM (96 vs
# 32 GB) — much of which is wasted at those configs. This case sits
# in the middle: 4K context per request stresses HBM-per-request more
# than 1024/1024 while still leaving headroom for high concurrency
# (128-256 max_num_seqs).
#
# max_num_seqs is the engines willingness to keep that many in-flight,
# not a pre-allocation. vllm sizes the KV pool against actual HBM and
# auto-caps the achieved concurrency. So setting max_num_seqs=1000 on
# v7x is safe even though 1000 seqs at full max_model_len wouldnt fit
# in HBM — the scheduler just runs fewer per step and queues the rest
# (same pattern weve always used on v6e). The companion specs sweep
# max_num_seqs up to 1000 so we can observe how throughput scales as
# the engine is allowed to use more of v7xs HBM-backed capacity.

: "${MODEL:=meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct}"
: "${TENSOR_PARALLEL_SIZE:=1}"
: "${NUM_Q_HEADS:=32}"
: "${NUM_KV_HEADS:=8}"
: "${HEAD_DIM:=128}"


: "${MAX_NUM_SEQS:=128}"
: "${MAX_NUM_BATCHED_TOKENS:=10275}"
: "${MAX_MODEL_LEN:=4096}"

# vLLM's --block-size (KV-cache page size). Empty = let vLLM pick its
# default. 128 wins on the all-three-flavors tune.
: "${BLOCK_SIZE:=128}"

: "${DATASET:=sonnet}"
: "${INPUT_LEN:=2048}"
: "${OUTPUT_LEN:=2048}"
: "${NUM_PROMPTS:=1000}"
